title: Tron McCarter, Cedar Creek crush Snyder
text:
Tron McCarter, Cedar Creek crush Snyder 
Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 9:55 pm | updated Thu, Oct 8, 2015 @ 10:04 pm The Florida Times-Union Cedar Creek's Tron McCarter had four touchdowns in Thursday's win over Bishop Snyder. 
Tron McCarter scored on three touchdown receptions and an interception return as the Saints routed Bishop Snyder 44-0 on Thursday night. 
McCarter has a combined seven touchdowns over his past two games. 
Sophomore quarterback Ivory Durham also threw four touchdown passes for Cedar Creek (5-1). 
Javon Williams rushed for 188 yards and a touchdown for the Saints. Snyder falls to 2-5. 
The win sends the Saints on to next weekâ€™s District 2-2A game at University Christian on a five-game winning streak.
